The paper deals with handling missing data in machine learning, which is a common problem in various subfields of computer science. However, the focus of the paper is on training neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the impact of missing data on predictive models, which is relevant to the subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the authors experimentally validate their proposed technique on benchmark datasets in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), indicating the potential applicability of their approach in these subfields. Finally, the paper proposes a new technique to handle missing data, which involves modifying the input data, which is a common approach in neural network training (cs.NE).
